  "title": "Broken Link found in `instantsearch.js` documentation",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\r\n\r\nI found a broken link for changelog in [instantsearch.js](https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/building-search-ui/what-is-instantsearch/js/#stay-up-to-date) documentation\r\n\r\nI know this is a very small change to be done and I would like to do the change myself but I could not find any way to contributing in the documentation. Am I missing something?🤔\r\n\r\n\r\nPS: There should a separate template for documentation related issues\r\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Go to [Stay up to date](https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/building-search-ui/what-is-instantsearch/js/#stay-up-to-date) section of '[What is InstantSearch.js?](https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/building-search-ui/what-is-instantsearch/js/)' page in the documentation\r\n2. Click on \"changelog\" link\r\n\r\n### 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nRedirect to [this](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/blob/master/packages/instantsearch.js/CHANGELOG.md) page\r\n\r\n### Code of Conduct\r\n\r\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct\r\n\r\n",
